subject: certificate-manager: supply configs from the repo
commitMessage:
certificate-manager: supply configs from the repo

This change is a part of the privilege seperation work
which is tracked in:
  https://github.com/openbmc/openbmc/issues/3383

This change should be merged after individual repo change:
  https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/phosphor-certificate-manager/+/41166

Signed-off-by: Anton D. Kachalov <gmouse@google.com>

We probably might want to create dedicated user instead of using dynamically allocated one and set ownership to the user instead of the group. Following with more restricted /etc/ssl/certs dir access to 0700.

Currently, bmcweb creates a /etc/ssl/certs/https/server.pem as root. This will lasts for a while (bmcweb needs privilege process to manage PAM). Perhaps, we should change bmcweb to set group ownership to certificate-manager with corresponding access rights).
ibm-hypervisor-cert missing

> meta-ibm/recipes-phosphor/certificate/phosphor-certificate-manager_%.bbappend:PACKAGECONFIG_append_witherspoon-tacoma = " ibm-hypervisor-cert"

It's enabled only for a specific platforms.
wow
assume these things went into repository
Yes, that is what being explained in the commit message.
i assume this is handled in the repo? need to look

"postinst" stuff is only about creating symlink to the service that is covered by the package itself.
the "prerm" has non-sense because it's never being executed in our env -- we do neither uninstall packages during rootfs creation nor support live package updates.

nit: Similar to another commit I mentioned this to, not sure if we want to tie the SRCREV bump before the dependent change actually goes in (to avoid over bumping / srcrev changing as it rebases while going in).

This is for CI purpose. Once the repo's change is merged, I have to update SRC_URI/SRCREV to reflect it. Some changes to individual repo is incompatible and have to be bumped within a separate change like this.
Are we sure it's going to break? The last 2 changes in phosphor-hwmon seemed ok - I'd rather separate out the bumps if possible

Let's see. It works for other changes by the luck :)
Particular this bump is for CI only.

Since https://github.com/openbmc/openbmc/blob/21e4b05f65aac96e8144594dc6dff6bf11ea356b/meta-quanta/meta-gbs/conf/machine/gbs.conf#L29, 
it needs to add OBMC_IMAGE_EXTRA_INSTALL:append:gbs = " phosphor-certificate-manager" here for gbs.
Done
I think this one needs a rebase and removal of the 'nobranch' now?
Done

Why does this new DEPENDS end up being necessary?  I would have thought it would be implied by some of the other dependencies.  If anything, I would expect an RDEPEND on dbus (daemon) and not a (build-time) DEPENDS.

Without this build dependency the build failed with the error:

ERROR: phosphor-certificate-manager-0.1+gitAUTOINC+6dd1c2ad86-r1 do_package: QA Issue: phosphor-certificate-manager: Files/directories were installed but not shipped in any package:
  /dbus-1
  /dbus-1/system.d
  /dbus-1/system.d/phosphor-bmcweb-cert-config.conf
  /dbus-1/system.d/phosphor-nslcd-authority-cert-config.conf
I don't understand.  Isn't that what the "FILES:" is for below?  There is no reason that a DEPENDS should affect what message you pasted here.

Ok.  The cause is this inside the makefile:

    configure.ac:        [with_dbuspolicydir=$($PKG_CONFIG --variable=sysconfdir dbus-1)/dbus-1/system.d])

That is kind of a poor way of finding where these go.

Can you clean this up?  Line 40 ends up blowing this away.  I assume there is a reason that CERT_TMPL is used as an indirection?  I don't actually see any use of the indirection in the repo, so maybe it is useless.
Done

Generally it is not a good idea to wholesale replace the FILES variable.  Can you `:append` to it what you need?  (I suspect it is simply dbus-1).

If we are going to need a dbus-1 added to the FILES path for many of these recipes we might want to make a bbclass to encapsulate it.
Done
